The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 23: Goldman Sachs is keen to set up a bank in the country and has approached the Reserve Bank of India for a licence. We have applied for a commercial bank licence. Our file is in now, Brooks Entwistle, chief executive officer and managing director of Goldman Sachs for India, said.                             
	 Mumbai, March 23: The Engineers India (EIL) board has approved the issue of bonus shares and a special dividend of Rs 100 per share, or 1,000 per cent. It also approved the sub-division of shares in the ratio of 1:2. One share of Rs 10 will be divided into two shares of Rs 5 apiece.                            
	 New Delhi, March 23: Uco Bank has cut down the issue size of its proposed follow-on offer to six crore shares against the earlier proposed size of 13.5 crore. The issue is expected to hit the markets in May.                             
	 New Delhi, March 23: Insurance regulator IRDA has warned the public not to buy life insurance policies from Mumbai-based Darwin Platform Life Insurance as the firm is not registered with it.                             
	 Mumbai, March 23: The BSE, NSE, forex and money markets will remain closed tomorrow on account of Ram Navami.
                                                                                                                          
